{
  "texts": [
    "The screening conditions for MRS spectra are described in Section 3.1, and the screening conditions for stellar sources are described in Section 3.2.",
    "In Section 3.3, we give statistical properties of the selected MRS time-domain sample of solar-like stars.",
    "The solar-like sample is selected by the stellar atmospheric parameters of the MRS spectra provided in the LAMOST MRS Parameter Catalog.",
    "In this work, we adopt the solar-like condition of 4500 K < T eff < 6500 K and log g > 4.1 dex, which includes the late F-type, G-type, and early K-type main-sequence stars.",
    "Since the stellar atmospheric parameters T eff, log g, and [Fe/H] (teff lasp, logg lasp, and feh lasp parameters in the catalog) and their uncertainties (denoted by δT eff, δ log g, and δ[Fe/H]) are extensively used in this work, we only keep the MRS spectra with all three atmospheric parameters and their uncertainties being available in the catalog."
  ]
}